I'm officially referring to today as do-over day. I got randomly selected for this 'Career Day' thing at work and while my CSM asked me if I'd be able to make it, I was pretty much told it was mandatory and I HAD to go. So much for asking if I can go. -__- It's technically on a day I never work not to mention in Torrington. Like I want to drive all the way to fucking Torrington for a Career Day thing I don't even WANT to do yet somehow HAVE to do. Why me? Seriously. Does it LOOK like I want to spend 8 hours at a seminar about career development? What am I in high school or something? Ugh. Ah well on the bright side of things, at least that's 8 hours of paid work. Like hell I'd go if I wasn't getting paid for it.On top of that, my drawer is off exactly $20 and I have NO idea why. That's going to be LOADS of fun if they can't figure out what is is. Yay write-up. Just what I've always wanted. OK here comes sucky thing number 2. So I get home grumbling about that only to find out that my cat passed away! I've known for a while that this day was coming but when you're already in a bad mood, totally does NOT help. She was terminally ill with FIV which is you guess it, the same as HIV only the feline version. My poor kitty. She's been suffering with it for a while so this is better in the long run but I still can't help but feel bad. My mom has been trying hard for weeks to keep my kitty alive, pretty much MAKING her eat and giving her kitty milk to keep her healthy. My poor mother. She does all this and of course my poor little Ebbie still falls victim to this stupid disease. I hate it and I hope I NEVER have to deal with this again. I don't think I can handle another case. This is now the second cat we've lost to the virus. The first one, my cat Misty, died from it two years ago when she was only 2 years old. Ebony originally was not diagnosed with the virus. She must have either gotten it from Misty or it didn't develop until later. Either way, the preventive shots they gave her to prevent her from getting the virus was apparently completely useless. So it's with a heavy heart that I say good bye to my little Ebony girl. Good bye Ebony. You've brought so much joy into this household these past 4 1/2 years and you'll always hold a special place in my heart. I'll always love you and never forget you and your crazy antics. We're burying you with your favorite toys, Thing 1 & 2 and your vampire fangs. Hope you play with them in Heaven and find your sister. She's been waiting 2 long years for you. Have fun with her like you used to. I know you missed her as much as I do but now you can play with her again. Sorry you couldn't live a nice life without this disease. I wish there was more we could do for you. Just remember that we loved you with all our hearts. Goodbye and don't worry, we'll meet again someday. Ugh can I have a do-over for today seriously? I want to wipe today from existence. Too bad, sadly the day is not even over yet. It's only 4:30. God I hope nothing else happens or I'll seriously freak out.

So it's almost Christmas. Given the time of night I'm writing this, we have about 9 days until Christmas Eve. -__- Holidays have a nasty habit of sneaking up on you unawares and scaring you. Haha the unawares is a reference to Pirates of the Caribbean since I recently purchased the 3rd film, At World's End. I have the really nice 2 disc special edition which is shockingly expensive compared to the last two. However, the box is incredibly nice looking...MUCH nicer than the other two and the discs inside are just as nice so it's no wonder they're asking for so much.
Back to the Christmas thing, I'm almost done shopping (yay). I have only my mom left and then fin.
Kaz just got a job working at the same store I am. He's going to be working in Photo/GM at Price Chopper. He says we're going to be the cutest couple in the store. -__- He's sometimes too sweet to handle. Gives you cavities heh. Price Chopper has cut back my hours yet I'm still somehow working my ass off, barely managing and somehow ALWAYS tired afterwards. I think it's just the added stress of the Holidays. Once the holidays are over, things should calm down a bit...well, maybe not. Seiji will be here by then. I'm looking forward to his coming here. Might be a breath of fresh air around here. Connecticut can be so stale sometimes.
Despite everything, I'm looking forward to Christmas. It looks like it's going to be a good one. Kaz seems to be really happy about it so far. He says it's the best Christmas he's had so far. I'm really excited for him too and for this Christmas in general. This'll be the first year I'll have someone to spend Christmas/New Year's with.
Ugh soo tired. Bed...now go.

DIR EN GREY COUNTDOWN T-MINUS 5 DAYS!!! *ahem* Anyway, anyone out there have a neato tophat I can borrow? Eh? Eh? Aw ya all suck! Boo.
I know it's been like a gabillion years since I updated this thing so I figured better now then...never.I feel like Michael Jackson. I have one glove on but one of the fingers on that hand is hurting like hell so I figured maybe warming it up would help? Yea shut up. Like I WANT to be wearing only ONE glove like a freak. It seems to be working though. That finger isn't hurting as much. 
I hate work but if I go into EZ-Scan rant mode, this journal entry will be much longer than I intended it to be so we'll leave that for another day. Ugh I feel like a real freakin idiot but oh well.
'Tis it for now....Oh yea, my Batman wallet is missing...so I now have a Jack Skellington one...it's purple and black I know you're jealous now. However, to whoever has my wallet, you owe me the $8 that was in my Batman wallet and another $9 for the new one. I'll be right here waiting so pay up dammit!

OK so I went to a concert lasy night and and it was amazing. One of the best tHrOnE shows ever. I even got Derek's guitar pick that he used during the concert and he signed it for me cuz he's the bestest ever! Hehe!
Anyway, aside from all that I got to hang out with people that I haven't in a while. Like all good things though, it had to end and now I'm all bored and not happy at all. I've been kinda saddy sad all day and I really don't know why...actually, I have a good idea and those that were with me probably know what it is but eh anyway whatever. Totally makes no damn difference to me whatsoever. After all, who cares what happens at concerts anyway? People act stupid and do and say things they don't mean all the time at them. Believe me I know cuz I'm guilty of it myself. 
Still, I still feel bad. -__- and I still wish someone would come over here and cheer me up...or SOMETHING!

School's out for SUMMER! Haha yay another semster at Tunxis squared away. -stretches- Feels good though I've already written down my classes for next year just got to get them registered and payed for. At least next semster, I get to have my best friend in class with me. Hehe that will be fun ^__^
I will be SO happy when finals are over and I can breathe or something! I think I'm going to go crash now see ya everyone! So TIRED!

Yet another poem written while ar work. It's amazing how easily you can be inspired when bored senseless at EZ-Scan oy do I HATE no hate isn't the word: LOATHE that's the word I loathe those things, Anyway, poem # 2 from work:

Fools
Who but fools?
Fools we are to love so easily.
To give ourselves whole heartedly to another person.
My what fools are we to love and lose and love again.
The vicious cycle of this thing we call love.
We suffer through for a fleeting emotion.
We are FOOLS.

Just some random poem I wrote at work...I was bored and I found some inspiration so I wrote it on some shitty reciept tape...

"Untitled"

Why do you stare?
You act like you care, but I know you don't.
You can't because no one ever does.
They all pretend those horrible liars.
None are worse than you,
To care, to not...makes no difference.
Doesn't change things.
You are still the worst...
Because of how much...
I care about you.

Well....I decided to FINALLY update this thing...resurrect it from the impending dead. OY...oh yeah MY BACKGROUND IS CLOUD!!!! Anyway, you really don't care so I'll just shut up. Anyway, I need to go to the Chinese buffet one day without my parents so I can tackle the guy I like that works there without my mom going "What the hell are you doing? Get over here!" or some random embarrassing thing. My mom doesn't understand how lonely I feel sometimes. I guess she doesn't think I'm ready for a relationship or whatever blah blah OKASHI! At any rate, I hate being alone. Loneliness has GOT to be the worst feeling in the world I mean I can't think of anything worse. I've been alone for a LOOOOONG time now and I'm wondering how much longer this is going to last. I don't know how much longer I can take this though. I mean, when you start thinking about tackling innocent waiters at buffet places, it's sad. Granted he has that cute Asian look going for him that I love..spikey hair haha sooo adorable. 
Gah I need a freakin life! Can anyone help me find one? Anyone? Please? *big silence* HELLO? *shrugs* I guess I really AM alone. *sigh* Well, I'm going to bed now where I can sulk in the dark...at least no one can see me there.

I AM VERY BORED AND I DON'T KNOW WHAT TO WRITE LALALALALA
haha that has got to be the lamest I've been in one of these things. Anyway, I realize I haven't written in this thing for a while so I decided to change that. Ebay is a wonderful invention but very bad potentially when you have a credit card heh. Anyway, the Good Charlotte/Simple Plan concert at Six Flags rocked. I couldn't see Paul though for most of it becaus poor Paul broke his leg or something. At any rate, he had a walking cast on that was freakin huge so he had to sit on a chair which kind of forced Good Charlotte to be a bit calmer than the normally are on stage but if they accidently hit Paul's leg, I don't think he would've appreciated it. David from Simple Plan was hysterical as expected and he looks wayyy better in person but then again, everyone usually does. My pictures came out funky and weird and I was rather far away and I'm only 5'2 so yea they aren't that great but I still remember things that I'll remember forever so that's all that really matters I guess. :) hehe I'm in such a dorky mood today. Dorky and bitchy strange combo I know but I'm strange so it works out I guess. *looks down at fingernails* Gah dammit I still haven't managed to paint them black yet! I will I must the plainess is begining to bother me.
T-E-E-N T-I-T-A-N-S TEEN TITANS LET'S GO!!! ok that was random and totally came out of nowhere. My brain just crapped that out of my head and if felt squishy. haha what a great quote that is. I just hope that's not all that I'm remebered for. That would suck but ok well. Wow for someone who opened with I don't know what to write lalalala I sure wrote a lot. I guess my brain does work on occasion. I can't really tell you anymore. I'm so stuffed up from being sick from the fuckin rain and cold that I can barely function right anymore and boy does it ever affect your appetite. I can't taste anything it all taste nasty ass except for chocolate which always seems to taste good somehow....ahh the wonders of chocolate. Mmmm MOMMY I WANT MY WONKA BAR!!!! wtf? Charlie and the Chocolate Factory doesn't come out until July. July 15th! GO SEE IT and make Tim Burton, Johnny Depp and Danny Elfman even more wealthy than they already are. You know you want to hehe for me? I would go opening day but the tHrOnE concert is the same day so scratch that to hell. I'll just have to go on Saturday or something if I'm not working ALL DAMN DAY!!!!!!
At any rate, my stomach is telling me to go eat so I suppose I should go satisfy it. Gah.

Yay I saw Green Day a few days ago and it was one HELL of a show! Billie Joe has NEVER looked better. I turned on TRL today and was surprised (well semi-surprised) to see the Backstreet Boys on there...and they BEAT Good Charlotte. I used to be OBSSESED with them when I was younger and it's good to see that they can make a comeback after being away for like what? 4 years or something like that? It's kind of surreal to see them again and rather successful at that. I'll be sure to buy their new album on JUNE 14TH!
Anyway, BACK TO GREEN DAY! Most people that actually bother to read this already know the details so I won't really get into them but God the $35 I paid to get in MORE than made up for itself that night.
Next concert: Good Charlotte and Simple Plan at Six Flags New England then followed (hopefully) by Level 27 Clothing presents: tHrOnE on July 15th at the Webster Underground!
I'm on the OFFICIAL LEVEL 27 STREET TEAM CALLED THE WALKING DEAD! It's pretty kick ass though for some unknown reason, I can't log into the site but that will hopefully be resolved shortly.

Well, I best get going. I've run out of things to be happy about and if I don't stop now, I'll have you guys crying before long. Oooh yea that and TEEN TITANS! is on yay!

~*Dawn*~

I need to update the background on here again. I get so bored with them sometimes that I ahve to change them or it drives me nuts. I have so many freakin pictures at home it's scary. Really freakin scary anyway, I have to go to class sooon :( I don't want to. It's math and I have a test dammit gah algebra is SOOOOO pointless. I don't plan on using it in my lifetime but yet they still insist that you take it stupid rules. Anyway, if I get out early from the test, I'll add in length to this, if not, I'll post new tonight when I change the background ang the link thingies whatever you call them and the title of the journal and everything like I always do. Not sure what I'm going to use this time as a background but I have a few ideas in mind. Feel free to leave me some ideas assuming someone reads this between now and when I get back on tonight around 8:30. Anyway, It's been fun, gotta run bye.

Have to go take a math test now! Ahhhh Damn school!

~*Dawn*~

Back from math test early think I did: AWFUL gah I'd be happy if I got a C or something. I don't respond well to D's or F's. Whenever I got them in the past, my brain like shuts down and it refuses to function right. As it is, it feels like it's been run through the blender a few times and is now officially mush lol gah I need to go shopping. It's quite the stress reliever well, depending no where you go I don't recommend Wal-Mart or a grocery store on the weekend heh but the mall is always fun and I need more manga it's the only thing that keeps me smart haha THERE'S A FUNNY THING: ME SMART? IMAGINE THAT!

From the very minute I picked her up as a kitten, we had a special bond. I raised her for nearly 2 years and she was my everything. I treated her like I would my own child and now that she's gone, I feel so alone. She was my everything and I feel a huge emptiness inside. I'm getting all teary eyed just trying to type this cuz it hurts so much. She was so young, too young to be taken from me and it just doesn't seem right to me. She was my baby, my world, my comfort when I felt alone and I needed her in so many ways...ways I never even realized until now. I loved her with every fiber of my being, my little kitty who I loved so dear. What am I going to do? Her sister misses her so much too, feel just as lost as I do I imagine. All she knows is that her sister went into the cage to go to the vet and never came back to her and it hurts my heart to see her wander around wondering where Misty is. My Misty Mountains who I will miss so much. Who will I share my french fries with now? Other cats will come and go, but she was the first one I owned myself and she was taken far too early. The vet told me that even though she had FIV, she could live a go 6-8 years. How is 2 years and 1 month 6 years? The disease took her from me. It progressed faster then they imagined it would. Just Sunday morning she was fine...last time I saw her as herself. I hate the world, the world that turned a human disease HIV into something cats can get too. I loved my cat and this just hurts so bad. I miss her so much. I think I need a hug.

To Misty: Love you always. I'll never forget you you crazy little thing you. I loved you dearly and until we meet again, this is goodbye. You brought me so much joy and love, made me so happy and now I can't stop crying. Just know that I love you and I'll see you again in Heaven.
